<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-30T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.653/124: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-30T10:00:00+01:00">September 30, 1939—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 30—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>433. Department’s telegram No. 83, August 30, 7 p.m. Director General
                                of Commerce in the Ministry of Trade and Foreign Exchange<note n="36" xml:id="d589fn36">M. Masi.</note> told the Commercial
                                Attaché yesterday that the premium which the Italian Government has
                                been paying on raw silk used in manufactured products is shortly to
                                be discontinued and that premiums will be retained only on raw silk
                                exported as such.</p>
                            <pb facs="0654" n="646" xml:id="pg_646"/>
                            <p>Masi intimated that in view of this change our Government might wish
                                to reconsider countervailing duties imposed on Italian silk
                                products.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>